User's Browser: The user's browser sends a request to access www.foobar.com.
Internet: The request travels through the internet to reach the DNS server.
DNS: The DNS server translates www.foobar.com to the IP address 8.8.8.8.
Single Server: The single server is hosting all the components:
Web Server (Nginx): Receives the request and serves static content or forwards dynamic content requests to the application server.
Application Server: Processes the business logic and serves dynamic content.
Application Files: The codebase for the application.
Database (MySQL): Stores and manages the application data.
